Join a team of caring and skilled professionals that are looking to make a
genuine difference to the lives of Early Childcare workers. We offer a
competitive salary, multiple benefits, and a friendly and creative atmosphere
designed to help you thrive.

** Our company **

Xap is a software platform designed to help ease the day-to-day running of
Early Childcare centres across Australia. Our mission is to not only have the
best software to serve this sector, but to also have the best people
supporting our customers. We want you to join us on this mission.

We pride ourselves on hiring people with deep expertise in either early
childhood education or IT – combined it ensures we deliver a premium service
to our customers.

_ ** Selection Criteria: ** _

  * Experience in a CCS Software and an understanding of CCS subsidies 
  * Aware of general office duties in a childcare environment and used a childcare management software or child learning software documentation tool. 
  * 3+ Years of experience working in the Early Childhood sector 
  * Good computer and analytical skills 
  * Excellent interpersonal communication skills to develop good relationships with children, families and staff 
  * Enjoy solving problems 
  * Willingness to learn and help customers 
  * Ability to set priorities, plan and organize own workload, with minimal supervision and excellent time management skills 

We aim to be a fun and vibrant place to work. We’re looking for like-minded
people who can really embrace and display the following four values:

** Warmth ** – you are nurturing and caring, and that comes across in everything you do. You support that with a layer of honesty and transparency that both your peers and customers will respect. 

** Courageous ** – you’re not afraid to try new ways of doing things or offering different perspectives. You’re confident to speak your mind and stand up for what you believe in, but also know how to pick your battles. 

** Determined ** – you strive to always be delivering the best for your customer and intuitively go that extra mile to ensure a positive result. You embrace change and seek ways to continuously improve. 

** Simplicity ** – you don’t overcomplicate situations and can easily translate seemingly complex scenarios into plain language. You actively seek ways of improving processes and realising new efficiencies. 

If the above sounds like you then forward a cover letter and your resume by
clicking on ** Apply for this job ** button on this page. We want to hear how
your drive and passion for our industry will help us on our mission.

